                                            ================
                                              Type Casting
                                            ================

-> Converting data from one data type to another data type is called Type Casting.
-> Type Casting is devided into 2 types..

1. Widening/ Up Casting
2. Narrowing/ Down Casting

-> The process of converting data from lower data type to higher data type is called as Widening/ Up Casting.
-> As we are converting lower data type to higher data type there is no data lose.
-> For widening no need to specify type casting explicitley. (JVM will take care of that ).
            
            byte b = 20;
            int i = b;
-> The process of converting data from higher data type to lower data type is called as Narrowing/ Down casting.
-> As we are converting higher data type to lower data type there is a chance of data loss.
-> For narrowing we need to specify type casting manually/ explicitley otherwise program can't be complied.

========
Example:
========
                  
                  package com.ibm.aadhar;
                  
                  public class TypeCasting {
                  
                  	
                  	public static void main(String[] args) {
                  		
                  		byte b = 20;
                  		int i = b;  // widening / up casting
                  		
                  		
                  		long num = 100;
                  		int j = (int) num; // narrowing / down casting
                  	}                                               
}

                                  ========================
                                  WORKING WITH STRING TYPE (string to int )
                                  ========================
                  
-> String type data can be converted to integer using Interger.parseInt(xx) method.
-> parseInt() is a static method available in integer Wrapper class.

Example: 



package com.ibm.aadhar;

public class TypeCastingString {
	
	public static void main(String[] args) {
		
		
		String s1 = args[0];
		String s2 = args[1];
		
		
		int i = Integer.parseInt(s1);
		int j = Integer.parseInt(s2);
		
		System.out.println(s1 + s2);
		
		System.out.println(i + j);
		
	}

}






